    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Recessed joints where a space is left between two members. An example is with joints in drywall or metal, where there is a narrow space between two adjoining panels, often allowing movement.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
